58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fstormofdragonsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=174.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hey Aggy</span><hr size=1> Yeah the guy who made that original post is a real jack-off. AoE isn't the problem, players are the problem. I still maintain that Verant gave us usable tools (AoEs) and that players are just too fookin lazy to learn how to use them. Most of them don't have enough neurons to rub together to coordinate anything more complex than mez-pull anyway. After all, when you mez-pull, you can have 1 guy do all the work.<br><br>It blows my mind that when somebody ISN'T too lazy, or decides that they want to take the extra risk to use the tools they were given (in this case AoEs), that Verant decides it's an exploit. Verant's mantra is &quot;risk vs. reward&quot;. AoEs are inherently more risky to do. Shouldn't the rewards be correspondingly greater?<br><br>So, why the fookin nerf?<br><br>In all fairness, this zone did need a tuning. It WAS a bit too easy. But instead of just making it harder through a reasonable method (upping HP a bit, increasing agro range slightly, giving the mobs nukes) they decided that AoEs are now against the &quot;Vision&quot;.<br><br>The main reason it was nerfed this way was is because a bunch of melee whined. There's 50 zones in the game where a wizard can't get a group at all. When just one zone shows up where a wizard becomes a commodity, it's taken away.<br><br>So that's why I now say: &quot;Hey Mr. Uberguild, go make yourself a pocket druid if you want a port. Why don't you ask one of the 700 strangers in your guild to help you?&quot; It's on a hotkey.<br><br>Aggy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6666cc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uaulinw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>aulinw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 151<br> <font color=#ffff00>(12/12/01 12:40:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fstormofdragonsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=174.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hey Aggy</span><hr size=1> lol I'm just sorry I wansnt able to test this out. I agree AoE spells are basically useless and when a use is found its all of a sudden bad. <p><a href ="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44548">Aulin Windrider</a> <BR>52 Wanderer <BR>Storm of Dragons <BR><BR><a href ="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=44583">Zurec Darkmist</a><BR>29 Necromancer <BR>Storm of Dragons <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6666cc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/usleezstakk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sleezstakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#ffff00>(12/12/01 1:07:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fstormofdragonsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=174.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hey Aggy</span><hr size=1> Now you're going too far my friend. AoE is not useless, it's just useless in the minds of melee players.<br><br>Melee are fantastic against 1 tough mob. As such, they only want to fight that way. In his mind, the only caster who's any good is the one who will turn the fight into a 1-on-1.<br><br>Nukers, however, are great against many wimpy mobs. Used correctly, AE can cut your raids down by at least 50% by eliminating yard trash and leaving the tough mobs to the tanks. But nobody uses it properly. Including us I might add, much to my constant utter disappointment.<br><br>AoE is not for quad kiting, AoE is not for powerlevelling. AoE is for removing yard trash in 15 secs so you can buff up your melee to take on that 100khp mob.<br><br>Frankly this is the problem: If tanks spent as much time learning how to work with casters as casters have spent learning how to work with tanks, we could do just about any raid in a couple hours tops.<br><br>But they won't, so I'm retiring.<br><br>Aggy (56th wiz, Retired) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6666cc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ucynsei.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cynsei</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 195<br> <font color=#ffff00>(12/12/01 4:06:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fstormofdragonsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=174.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hey Aggy</span><hr size=1> Not useless in the mind of this melee'ah. In fact, I'm a proponet of it.<br><br>I play on BB server also and in Fear one night Club Fu came in and used the AE tactic. They had 4 monks pullin non stop into a group of AEers. Was fuggin amazing, they cleared the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> whole</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> zone in under two hours. Except for the eight or so mobs we got lucky enough to snag.<br><br>I'd like to see us try it more often honestly. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6666cc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/bstormofdragons.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=squarrauqs>Squar Rauqs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 330<br> <font color=#ffff00>(12/12/01 11:23:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/fstormofdragonsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=174.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hey 